15/08/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The deputy director general of the Turkish Police, Ramazan Er, said Friday (13 August) that authorities believe the former Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), now known as KONGRA-GEL, was behind last week’s bombings in Istanbul. 
Tuesday’s blasts at two small hotels and a gas plant left two dead and several injured. 
According to Turkish media, police are searching for Kurdish militants in connection with new threats of bomb attacks. 
(Anadolu Agency, AFP - 13/08/04)
